p: \rVery well, \pn.\nIf you're ready to take on Lugia, then let's begin!
\r...I must say, I'm impressed.\nYou defeated both Lugia and my Crawdaunt.
\rFine. I'll let you go.\nIt really is a shame you're working against us rather than with us.
\rIt's time to move on to the next phase.
\rVery well, \pn.\nIf you're ready to take on Lugia, then let's begin!
\r...I must say, I'm impressed.\nYou defeated both Lugia and my Crawdaunt.
\rFine. I'll let you live... for now.\nBut be warned, \pn, if you ever cross my path again, I might not be so merciful.
\rIt's time to move on to the next phase.
\rI was getting worried you wouldn't show up.
\rAfter all, we wouldn't want to start without our special snowflake hero, would we?
\rThe Whirl Islands are home to one of the oldest living creatures.
\rLugia, the guardian of the sea, the Stormslinger.
\rIt hasn't graced us with its presence since the days of Gold...
\rBut now, the Whirl Islands- its home- have returned.
\rThe domain of a legendary Pokemon isn't an ordinary place...\nIt's connected to that Pokemon's artifact.
\rIt's why the Hall of Origin only appeared to Dawn when she brandished the Azure Flute.
\rAnd now that I have the Bell, it'll bend to my will.
\rNow, emerge, Lugia! You will be mine!
\rMy name is Audrey. I am the leader of the Abyssal Cult.\nWith your strength, and my leadership, this planet could be ours.
\rWe have great plans for the world, Lugia, but we need your help to pull them off.
\rWhat do you say? Will you join us? Will you work under me?
\rAre you satisfied?\nDid you see what you came to see?
\rOf course you aren't. You'll want to battle.\nBut here's the thing...
\rEven if you win, it's not like I'll release Lugia and leave.\nWhy would I? Beating me won't change a thing.
\rYou win, you get nothing, but if I win, you lose everything.
\rI'll give you a chance to prepare.\nI won't indignify the Stormslinger by having it fight a weakened opponent.\nLet me know when you're ready to battle.

\bHonestly, I just joined the cult for the sweet outfits.
